    A["A (root)"] --&gt; B["B (removed)"]
    B --&gt; C["C (surviving)"]
    B --&gt; D["D (removed)"]
    A --&gt; E["E (surviving)"]




Figure 7.1: Before contraction: node B is marked for removal, but its child C survives.





After contraction, C is re-parented to A:






